1. Aftercare following surgery Z48.89
She is here today for an ORIF of the right lateral malleolus and reduction internal fixation of the right fifth metatarsal. Patient is doing fairly well. She will remain nonweightbearing. She was put in a boot today. Staples were removed atraumatically. Patient will not shower her foot for 24 hours but will not submerge in water for at least 7 days. Patient will follow up in 4 weeks time with x-rays upon arrival.
